%I A394653 #51 Jun 14 2026 22:21:16
%S A394653 27,30,600,891
%N A394653 Integers x such that there exist four integers 0<x<=y<=z and 0<t<=w such that sigma(x)*psi(x)*phi(x)^2 = sigma(y)*psi(y)*phi(y)^2 = sigma(z)*psi(z)*phi(z)^2 = x^3 + y^3 + z^3 + t^3 + w^3.
%C A394653 The numbers x, y, z, t and w form a sigma*psi*phi^2-cubic quintuple. Is it possible that x=y=z does not hold?
%H A394653 S. I. Dimitrov, <a href="https://github.com/Stoyan16/Sigma-psi-phi-2-cubic-quintuples/blob/main/A394653">Python program</a> (GitHub)
%e A394653 (27, 27, 27, 54, 63) is such a quintuple because sigma(27) * psi(27) * phi(27)^2 = 40 * 36 * 18^2 = 3 * 27^3 + 54^3 + 63^3. Other quintuples are (30, 30, 30, 9, 63), (600, 600, 600, 120, 4080) and (891, 891, 891, 1647, 8154).
%o A394653 (Python) # See Links.
%Y A394653 Cf. A000010, A000203, A001615, A003328, A386378, A391535, A396458, A396564, A396635.
%K A394653 nonn,hard,more
